"{\"uid\": \"gbnews.com-sport-olympics-kishane-thompson-robbed-olympics-noah-lyles-wins-100m-gold\", \"text\": \"Man City win Carabao Cup after Arsenal's major goalkeeping error  Kishane Thompson narrowly missed out on the 100m gold medal at the Paris Olympics on Sunday night  PA  ByJack Otway,  Published: 05/08/2024  Updated: 05/08/2024  Sunday's big event lived up to the billing as Noah Lyles claimed gold in Paris  Fans of the Olympics have vented their fury, with some believing Jamaican star Kishane Thompson deserved the gold medal instead of Noah Lyles following the 100-metre race last night.  Lyles won on Sunday evening by just five thousandths of a second in arguably the most exciting 100m race of all time.  A photo finish was required to establish who had won the flagship event, with Lyles eventually given the victory with a time of 9.79 seconds.Having won bronze in Tokyo three years ago, it was a crowning moment for the American.Kishane Thompson narrowly missed out on the 100m gold medal at the Paris Olympics on Sunday night|PABut some on social media feel Thomspon deserved the win instead, with one user saying: \\\"Thompson was robbed. He beat Noah.\\\"\\\"Not even being bitter but I think Kishane Thompson got robbed by Noah Lyles,\\\" were the words of a second.A third said: \\\"Kishane Thompson has been robbed in broad daylight.\\\"Another opined: \\\"I still do not think Lyles won this race. Thompson was robbed here.\\\"JUST IN:Imane Khelif makes feelings clear as controversial Olympics star lashes out amid gender scrutinyAnd a fifth said: \\\"Congratulations Kishane Thompson you won gold medal in my books. He crossed before Noah if we are being honest. He got robbed this one (sic).\\\"More users have jumped to the defence of the Jamaica star.Another stated: \\\"Do not understand the rules but the Jamaican was there first.\\\"And another said: \\\"Is it head first to win? Thompsons foot clearly over.\\\"READ MORE:Graham Thorpe dies aged 55 as tributes to England cricket icon pour inWhen it comes to track events, the winner is the first person to get their chest across the line.While Thompson's foot was across the line ahead of Lyles, it was the Team USA star who got his chest over first.Speaking after his win, meanwhile, Lyles expressed his joy at winning the first Olympic gold medal of his career.\\\"It's the one I wanted, it's the hard battle, the amazing opponents, everybody was healthy and came to fight,\\\" he said.LATEST SPORTS NEWS:Rory McIlroy called out by Olympics rival after 's***show' remark as Tommy Fleetwood misses out on goldAdam Peaty wants 'cheating' Chinese athletes kicked out of Paris Olympics after 4x100m relay goldBBC cause outrage after scrapping coverage of Novak Djokovic vs Carlos Alcaraz midway through Olympic finalKishane Thompson crossed the line with his foot first but not his chest as Noah Lyles won 100m gold|PA\\\"I am the wolf among wolves. I will be honest, I went to Kishane, I said, 'I will be honest, I think you had that one'.\\\"I was prepared to see his name pop up. I saw my name pop up and I said, goodness gracious, I am incredible.\\\"He continued: \\\"I am still moving forward and moving forward, when the time came and I was saying: this is the final and I am going to need to go out there and do it.\\\"I wasn't ready to see it (my name pop up) I am going to be honest that's the first time that I wasn't ready to see it, he was quite a few lanes down so it was quite hard for me to picture where we were, but I guess that was a good thing.\\\"Noah Lyles won 100m gold on Sunday by narrowly beating Kishane Thompson|PALyles is also set to compete in the 200m.But he's convinced he's the quickest man in the world right now, with the 27-year-old adding: \\\"What's the title of Olympic champion? [The fastest man on the planet?] Amen.\\\"  A photo finish was required to establish who had won the flagship event, with Lyles eventually given the victory with a time of 9.79 seconds.  Having won bronze in Tokyo three years ago, it was a crowning moment for the American.  Kishane Thompson narrowly missed out on the 100m gold medal at the Paris Olympics on Sunday night  PA  But some on social media feel Thomspon deserved the win instead, with one user saying: \\\"Thompson was robbed. He beat Noah.\\\"  \\\"Not even being bitter but I think Kishane Thompson got robbed by Noah Lyles,\\\" were the words of a second.  A third said: \\\"Kishane Thompson has been robbed in broad daylight.\\\"  Another opined: \\\"I still do not think Lyles won this race. Thompson was robbed here.\\\"  JUST IN:Imane Khelif makes feelings clear as controversial Olympics star lashes out amid gender scrutiny  And a fifth said: \\\"Congratulations Kishane Thompson you won gold medal in my books. He crossed before Noah if we are being honest. He got robbed this one (sic).\\\"  More users have jumped to the defence of the Jamaica star.  Another stated: \\\"Do not understand the rules but the Jamaican was there first.\\\"  And another said: \\\"Is it head first to win? Thompsons foot clearly over.\\\"  READ MORE:Graham Thorpe dies aged 55 as tributes to England cricket icon pour in  When it comes to track events, the winner is the first person to get their chest across the line.  While Thompson's foot was across the line ahead of Lyles, it was the Team USA star who got his chest over first.  Speaking after his win, meanwhile, Lyles expressed his joy at winning the first Olympic gold medal of his career.  \\\"It's the one I wanted, it's the hard battle, the amazing opponents, everybody was healthy and came to fight,\\\" he said.  LATEST SPORTS NEWS:  Kishane Thompson crossed the line with his foot first but not his chest as Noah Lyles won 100m gold  PA  \\\"I am the wolf among wolves. I will be honest, I went to Kishane, I said, 'I will be honest, I think you had that one'.  \\\"I was prepared to see his name pop up. I saw my name pop up and I said, goodness gracious, I am incredible.\\\"  He continued: \\\"I am still moving forward and moving forward, when the time came and I was saying: this is the final and I am going to need to go out there and do it.  \\\"I wasn't ready to see it (my name pop up) I am going to be honest that's the first time that I wasn't ready to see it, he was quite a few lanes down so it was quite hard for me to picture where we were, but I guess that was a good thing.\\\"  Noah Lyles won 100m gold on Sunday by narrowly beating Kishane Thompson  PA  Lyles is also set to compete in the 200m.  But he's convinced he's the quickest man in the world right now, with the 27-year-old adding: \\\"What's the title of Olympic champion? [The fastest man on the planet?] Amen.\\\"  \"}"